  <title>SENIOR LECTURER/LECTURER-EMERGENCY MEDICINE</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/senior-lecturerlecturer-emergency-medicine</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;SENIOR LECTURER/LECTURER-EMERGENCY MEDICINE&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;span lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/2085" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" xml:lang=""&gt;maribek&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Thu, 27/02/2020 - 16:57&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Emergency Medicine&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 13 Mar. 2020&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FACULTY OF MEDICINE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;DEPARTMENT OF EMERGENCY MEDICINE&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VACANCY NO: FM/EM 2/2020, SENIOR LECTURER OR LECTURER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties:&lt;/strong&gt; The successful candidates will; &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; teach undergraduate medical students and postgraduate residents; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; conduct research in his/her areas of expertise and supervise medical students’ research projects; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; provide service to the university, profession and community; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; provide clinical care in affiliated hospitals; and &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; carry out any other duties as assigned by the head of the department.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Lecturer:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; at least a Bachelor of Medicine/Bachelor of Surgery or other recognized Medical doctor qualification (MD); &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; a specialist qualification in Emergency Medicine with a minimum of 3 years post-specialization experience in professional practice in Emergency Medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(iii) &lt;/strong&gt;The qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; evidence of professional specialization in any field of medicine and evidence of active license to practice where appropriate; &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;6&lt;/strong&gt; pieces of research products published by recognized publishers,&lt;strong&gt; 3&lt;/strong&gt; of which must be articles in refereed/ accredited journals in internationally recognized indexing databases; (iv) paper/poster presentation at national and/or international conferences, depending on the discipline; &lt;strong&gt;(vi)&lt;/strong&gt; be lead and/ or last author in at least  (2 of 3) refereed journal publications; &lt;strong&gt;(vii)&lt;/strong&gt; publications should be spread nationally and/or internationally and across journals; &lt;strong&gt;(viii)&lt;/strong&gt; some research impact, including but not limited to citations, the h-index, patents, policy applications, peer reviews, publications that are prescribed texts in other institutions etc. (required in at least 1 of the these); &lt;strong&gt;(ix)&lt;/strong&gt; recognized as being of at least national research or effective clinical professional standing (e.g. reviewer for refereed/accredited national and regional publishers, Editorial board member of at least national publisher in a relevant field, invitation as keynote speaker at national and international conferences/symposia. (Required in at least 1 of these); &lt;strong&gt;(x)&lt;/strong&gt; active maintenance of a license to practice issued by the relevant professional licensing authority; successful supervision/co-supervision of research projects/ Post-doctoral/clinical research fellow supervision; &lt;strong&gt;(xi)&lt;/strong&gt; evidence of social engagement and governance; &lt;strong&gt;(xii) &lt;/strong&gt;Sustained professional research output ; a minimum of 1 peer reviewed publication every 2 years or 2 new CPW every 6 years or since last promotion shall constitute sustained research output; &lt;strong&gt;(xiii)&lt;/strong&gt; Paper/poster/creative professional presentation at national and/or regional conferences&lt;strong&gt;; (xiv)&lt;/strong&gt; Successful supervision/co-supervision of research projects/post-doctoral/clinical research.  The following will be added advantages: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; sustained research activity; on-going internally and externally-funded research activity; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; research/clinical effectiveness awards and other forms research recognition; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; examiner for undergraduate and/ or postgraduate projects nationally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lecturer&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; at least a Bachelor of Medicine/Bachelor of Surgery or other recognized Medical doctor qualification (MD); &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; a specialist qualification in Emergency Medicine; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; The qualification must be registerable by the Botswana Health Professions Council with a specialist status; &lt;strong&gt;(iv)&lt;/strong&gt; Evidence of governance and social engagement; &lt;strong&gt;(v)&lt;/strong&gt; experience of teaching at a university or comparable institution will be an added advantage&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attributes and skills required; &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent communication and organizational skills; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; Strong academic leadership skills and sympathy for the values and culture of the University; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; Good management, human relations and sound analytical and coordinating skills.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remuneration: &lt;/strong&gt;The University offers competitive salaries and benefits commensurate with experience and qualification&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to apply:&lt;/strong&gt; Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the university determine their suitability for the position.  They should provide current CV’s (including telephone and e-mail), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, and THREE (3) reference letters.  Applicants should inform their referees to:  (i) Quote the position applied for and (ii) submit their references directly to the address below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Human Resources Manager, Faculty of Medicine, Corner of Notwane and Mabuto Road, University of Botswana, Private Bag 00713 Gaborone, Botswana; or Email to nkangana@mopipi.ub.bw  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hand delivered applications should be sent to Faculty of Medicine,&lt;strong&gt; UB Teaching Hospital, 3rd Floor, Office F 4003&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NB:  Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/p&gt;

